cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with temporal logics and their extensions. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the expressivity of different logics and their ability to express certain properties. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the extension of CTL to arbitrary language classes. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may be relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the extended CTL framework. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) may also be relevant as the paper discusses the use of CTL and its extensions in automated verification, which is a common software engineering task.
